<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-7631] @CompileStatic compiles 0 != null to false</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-7631</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;import groovy.transform.*;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;// @CompileStatic&lt;br/&gt;
class Bug {&lt;br/&gt;
    void exec() &lt;/p&gt;
{
        println 0 != null
    }
&lt;p&gt;}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;new Bug().exec()&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#8203;The above code prints &quot;true&quot;. But when @CompileStatic is umcommented, it prints &quot;false&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
